olive oil
½ tin sweetcorn
2 brioche hotdog buns
1 packet pulled chicken
1 sachet All-American Spice Blend
1 packet BBQ sauce
1 packet mayonnaise
1 packet Dijon mustard
1 tsp honey
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Drain sweetcorn.
• Split brioche hotdog buns in half lengthways.
• Heat a large frying pan over high heat. Cook corn kernels until lightly browned, 4-5 minutes. Transfer to a large bowl.

TIP: Cover the pan with a lid if the kernels are “popping” out.

• Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook pulled chicken and All-American spice blend, breaking up with a spoon, until browned,
3-4 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, add BBQ sauce and a splash of water and stir to combine. Season to taste.

• Toast brioche hot dog buns as desired.
• In a small bowl combine mayonnaise, dijon mustard and the honey.
• To the bowl with the corn, combine shredded cabbage mix, mixed salad leaves, half the mustard mayonnaise and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil. Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese and toss to combine. Season to taste.

• Spread bun bases with remaining mustard mayonnaise. Fill buns with pulled chicken and cheesy corn slaw.
• Divide cheesy Texan-style BBQ pulled chicken buns between plates.
• Serve with any leftover corn slaw. Enjoy!